# Server on port 4122 — restart after every change

**Standing user preference:** Whenever you modify this project (any code, templates, CSS, JS, or `go.mod`), **rebuild and restart the server on `127.0.0.1:4122` before you finish the turn** — not only on request. Treat this as part of “done” for the task.

Applies to: Go (`cmd/`, `internal/`, …), `web/templates`, `web/static`, `migrations`, config that affects runtime.

**Exceptions:** User explicitly says not to restart; or they are running **`air`** / `dev-watch` and you confirm it is already rebuilding. If unsure, restart anyway.

**Do not** end with “restart it yourself” after you changed files — **run the restart** (or delegate to a one-line background `go run` after freeing the port).

## Windows (PowerShell)

From the **`REMI Trip Planner`** directory (module root with `go.mod`):

```powershell
$p = Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 4122 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 1 -ExpandProperty OwningProcess
if ($p) { Stop-Process -Id $p -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
go build -o bin/remi-server.exe ./cmd/server
$env:APP_ADDR = "127.0.0.1:4122"
Start-Process -FilePath ".\bin\remi-server.exe" -WorkingDirectory (Get-Location) -WindowStyle Hidden
```

Confirm listen: `netstat -ano | findstr ":4122"` (or `Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 4122`).

## Do not

- End with “run it yourself” when you changed code — **run the restart** (unless `air` is handling it).
- Skip restart after template/CSS/JS-only edits — the running binary may not need rebuild, but **restarting** still picks up static files from disk; **rebuild** when Go changed.

Docker deploy (`docker compose`) is optional; the user’s standing preference for local dev is **native `go build` + `APP_ADDR=127.0.0.1:4122`** (use `APP_ADDR=:4122` only if they need LAN access).
